# A counterexample for the reverse direction: a mortal who is not a man.
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> rex is a mortal
< Learned: mortal(rex).
# Induce: every man is mortal (2+ examples, no counterexample); NOT the
# reverse (rex is mortal but not a man), and NOT dog->mortal (only 1 example).
> generalize
< Induced: mortal(X) :- man(X).
# The induced rule generalizes to a brand-new individual never seen as mortal.
